Fastest option: copy source + Docker build on server
On your local machine, create a clean archive (excludes node_modules, .next, SQLite dev database):

cd /home/agiusti/Nextcloud/Projetos/Scriptum
tar --exclude='node_modules' --exclude='.next' --exclude='prisma/dev.db' -czf /tmp/scriptum.tar.gz .

Copy to the server:
scp /tmp/scriptum.tar.gz user@your-server:/opt/scriptum.tar.gz

On the server:
mkdir /opt/scriptum
cd /opt/scriptum
tar -xzf /tmp/scriptum.tar.gz

cp .env.example .env
nano .env   # set the three required values below
Minimum .env for production:


NEXTAUTH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 32)   # paste the output
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-password
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://your-server-ip:3000      # or https://your-domain.com

Then build and start:
docker compose up -d --build

First build takes 3–5 minutes. The container auto-runs prisma db push before starting. Open http://your-server-ip:3000 and register the first account.

What you need on the server
Docker 24+ and Docker Compose v2+ — nothing else. Chromium, PostgreSQL, and Node are all inside the containers.
If you have a domain + want HTTPS

After the app is running:
apt-get install certbot python3-certbot-nginx
# configure Nginx to proxy :3000 (see INSTALL.md for the exact config)
certbot --nginx -d your-domain.com

Then update NEXTAUTH_URL=https://your-domain.com in .env and docker compose up -d.

Future updates
# on the server, after copying new source
docker compose up -d --build

Schema changes are applied automatically on startup via prisma db push.
